Job Description:
* Objective:
- Marketing Manager is expected to exhaust all the marketing strategies to promote CAM-ASEAN brand to it furthest possible and generate new customers with expectation of doubling the number of current students.

-	Managing all marketing for the company and activities within the marketing department;
- Developing the marketing strategy for the company in line with company objectives;
- Co-ordinating marketing campaigns with sales activities;
-	Overseeing the company’s marketing budget;
- Creation and publication of all marketing material in line with marketing plans;
-	Planning and implementing promotional campaigns;
-	Manage and improve lead generation campaigns, measuring results;
- Overall responsibility for brand management and corporate identity;
- Preparing online and print marketing campaigns;
-	Monitor and report on effectiveness of marketing communications;
- Creating a wide range of different marketing materials;
-	Working closely with design agencies and assisting with new product launches;
- Maintain effective internal communications to ensure that all relevant company functions are kept informed of marketing objectives;
-	Analyzing potential strategic partner relationships for company marketing.
-Organize market research studies and analyze the findings (Competitors)
-Develop pricing strategies and promotion for products to be marketed, keeping the client’s budget balanced with the firm’s needs
- Research and evaluate new product opportunities, demand for potential products, and customer needs and insights
-	Devise, create, and implement multi-prong advertising campaigns, including use of TV, newspaper, magazines, internet, publics seminars, fairs, conventions and sales events
-	Attend networking events to develop business contacts and expand the awareness of CAM-ASEAN and the course and services provided
- Conduct student surveys to gain insight and determine if their needs and expectations are being met and what services or programs can be developed to increase student satisfaction and sales
-	Analyze monthly sales results (student enrollment) and customer enquiry activity to gauge marketing effectiveness and to identify future trends and business opportunities
-	Perform all other relevant tasks associated with Sales & Marketing  
- Tracks competitors’ product promotions, sales and marketing activities by researching events & announcements in related industry
- Discover and explore opportunities to collaborate with potential partners
-	Enhances organization’s reputation and explore opportunities to add value to job accomplishments
-	Attend all meetings required by CAM-ASEAN;
-	Prepare and provide end of the month activity undertaken and status report and submit to Head of Marketing no later than the 3rd (third) day of the following month 
- Perform other tasks assigned by immediate superior

Job Requirement:
- Having minimum 2-year related work experience (Advantage);
- Holding at least a bachelor’s degree or equivalent certificate (Master is preferred).
- Good knowledge of relevant computer application with good English;
-	Good communication and interpersonal skills, teamwork and professionalism. 

